Step 1: Copy the Application File
From your Jump Host, copy the .war file to the target App Server (e.g., stapp03) using scp
scp /tmp/ROOT.war banner@stapp03:/tmp/
Step 2: Install Tomcat
Log into the target App Server, switch to the root user, and install Tomcat
sudo yum install -y tomcat tomcat-webapps
sudo systemctl enable tomcat
Step 3: Configure the Port
Tomcat runs on port 8080 by default. If the task requires a custom port (e.g., 8082 or 5001), edit the server.xml file
sudo vi /etc/tomcat/server.xml
Find the <Connector> tag and change the port attribute to your assigned requirement. 
Step 4: Deploy the App & Start Service
Move the .war file to the Tomcat webapps directory and start the service
sudo cp /tmp/ROOT.war /usr/share/tomcat/webapps/
sudo chown tomcat:tomcat /usr/share/tomcat/webapps/ROOT.war
sudo systemctl start tomcat
Step 5: Verify
Return to your Jump Host and verify the deployment using curl:
curl http://stapp03:<port>
